When I was a 20 year old sophomore at Franklin College in Indiana, I was living in the basement of Bryan Residence Hall when the dormitory burned down on May 16, 1985. I lost most of my possessions in life. If there ever was a single event, that one strongly influenced the direction I was taking into adulthood, and is in many ways responsible for who I am now.
